text: British Columbia Highway 5A (Highway 5A) also known as the Princeton-Kamloops Highway is a highway in British Columbia that alternative to Highway 5. It is concurrent with Highway 97C near Merritt. Between Merritt and Kamloops, Highway 5A acts a bypass around Highway 5. Its south end is at with a traffic light with Highway 3 at Princeton while the north end is at with a junction with Highway 1 at Kamloops. ==Related pages== *British Columbia Highway 5 Category:British Columbia provincial highways Category:Interior of British Columbia Category:Nicola Country
